-- Sanoma Corp Said to Sell 300 Million Euros of Five-Year Notes
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-03-13T08:57:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/sanoma-corp-said-to-sell-300-million-euros-of-five-year-notes.html
Sanoma Corporation is selling 300
million euros of senior unsecured five-year notes, according to
a banker involved in the deal.  The bonds will be priced to yield about 375 basis points
more than the benchmark mid-swap rate.  BNP Paribas SA, ING Groep NV and Nordea Bank are managing
the transaction.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah Benjamin in London at 
 hbenjamin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Shanahan at 
 mshanahan3@bloomberg.net  